result.adr_address: 146 Wan Chai Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 146 Wan Chai Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Bafang Dumpling

reviews.text: Quick, easy and tasty. Seats turnover quickly, so don't go if a lazy chat is part of your plan. This place is all about fast, afforable and tasty.

I love to come here to grab boiled dumplings. There is a fair choice of different dumplings, taiwanese dishes and many sets to choose from. 

They rebranded the concept a few months ago and this help making it a bit more attractive. The menu is well designed with photos and English and Chinese.

The restaurant is small so I usually take away. The dumplings are tasty and the staff is very friendly.
Quite tasty! Good service.

I used to frequent Bafang in Shenzhen quite often. I love it. It is consistently solid, and never disappoints. 

The flavor and quality are slightly above average. 

Bafang, I will also stop by when we cross paths.

Worst food in Hong Kong! Perhaps the dumplings are nice but we opted for the spicy and sour soup. It was not spicy and it was not sour at all. The Taiwan rice noodles turned out to be some sort of extremely smelly soup that made me lose my appetite had a very strange taste like it was off.

result.formatted_address: 8 Wo Mun St, Fanling, Hong Kong
result.name: Regentville Shopping Centre

reviews.text: Small local mall. Not visited by mainlanders with suitcases. Pleasant.
Good place to shop daily living needs,  supermarket, drug store, electrical appliance, clothing and restaurant, etc. Also have hourly carpark services.
Very good on eating,but so many sale clothes shop

Ordinary Hong Kong shopping centre. There is the supermarket (Wellcome) and the seafood restaurant as well as the usual crop of chain shops, clothes shops and mobile phones and accessories. The best thing is the direct access to the wet market.
There is nothing special, a shopping place for people living in the area.
Nice clean shopping centre. Has a lot of shops and a few places for dining from Pizza, Restaurant, Noodles and other fast food chains. Not overly crowded, easy to move around.
